Title: Parted in Anger
Description: Speak to members of the Cult of Renewal to learn what happened to Han Fang's daughter, Han Liu.
ObjectiveProposalResponse: How embarrassing. Yes.\n\nThis is all so personal, and you a total stranger, but my daughter Han Liu has vanished. She was invited to share a meal with some strangers and simply did not come home.
InProgressResponse: I know I ask a great deal of you, stranger. You have my family's gratitude. Please bring my daughter back to me.
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: You return! Did they speak to you? I cannot fathom they would turn you away as well. You do not have that "hovering mother" look about you.

Title: The Cult of Renewal
Description: Find Han Liu by joining her on the Cult of Renewal's so-called "Path of Truth."
ObjectiveProposalResponse: They would. How like a cult to both prevent me from speaking to her after she was in their clutches and then immediately send her away to prove herself.\n\nAnd how very like Liu to leap to impress…
InProgressResponse: I only hope we are not too late.\n\nHeadstrong, foolish child…
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: I cannot tell you what a relief it is to see another on the road. I was truly beginning to worry I would need to continue on alone!

Title: Walking Wyrds
Description: Complete your own Path of Truth by planting an imbued seed at each of the Angry Earth shrines within the Wyrdwood Twists. Help Han Liu do the same by clearing the path of Angry Earth.
ObjectiveProposalResponse: My mother? She truly cannot mind her own affairs, can she? This is MY choice. \n\nThose people were kind to me. All I want to do is learn more about them!
InProgressResponse: I can climb well enough, but I am afraid I am rather useless in a fight. I hope for both our sakes that you are equipped to handle this.
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: Forgive me for being so cryptic before. This trial is certainly not for the faint of heart, but it does help us find those who truly think and feel as we do. I'm eager to hear about your journey.

Title: Spoken Wyrds
Description: Talk to Han Fang about taking the oath to officially join the Cult of Renewal.
ObjectiveProposalResponse: You have, but in deed only. I have seen your commitment to understanding what it is we are doing here and it has been noted.\n\nBut here, we believe words hold power as well. Miss Liu has already spoken hers.
InProgressResponse: The High Sage spoke those words to me when first we met. I felt them so stark, so prescient, that I saved them for all to come.
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: Welcome to the Cult of Renewal, my friend. I now name you Initiate, and soon all of our knowledge will be yours.\n\nEnjoy the grounds. Celebrate. Rest. You will be called upon when you are ready for the next step.

Title: A Sword in my Stead
Description: Try to talk Han Liu out of undergoing a difficult rite and help her succeed if she insists on going anyway.
ObjectiveProposalResponse: She mentioned yet another trial, this time to one of those dryad-infested towers! I need not remind you how utterly defenseless she is!\n\nI pushed too hard to keep her here, to stop her. She told me to stay away.
InProgressResponse: What on Aeternum is this cult after? It feels to me as if they are trying to get their followers killed.\n\nOh Liu… why won't you listen?
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: What a triumph. In so little time both you and Miss Liu have not only demonstrated a willingness to learn, but also a deep, abiding respect for the denizens of Edengrove.\n\nFor this, we place our full trust in you.

Title: One of Us
Description: Venture to Buggane Hedge and harvest herbs for a calming tea from the hides of dryads.
ObjectiveProposalResponse: Like myself and the High Sage, and the scores of Exalted, they will have gained the deepest, most complete understanding of our way of life. They will then go forth into Aeternum and tell others what they found.
InProgressResponse: I find a calming tea helps center them, opens their mind to the experience they are about to have.\n\nIt also helps reduce any mishaps with the denizens of the forest they are about to wander into.
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: This is a fine bundle of herbs. I hope you did not have a great deal of trouble acquiring them- it is a tricky task at best, and I have never met a dryad that gave them willingly.\n\nI will brew the tea, now.

Title: Something to Celebrate
Description: Venture into the verdant forests of Edengrove to harvest colorful flowers in celebration of the returning cultists.
PlayerPrompt: "What happens if they do not return?"
ObjectiveProposalResponse: Ah… I would prefer not to darken the mood with that discussion. I will, but not now. In this moment I would like to assume they will succeed. Can you procure some bright flowers, so we can make wreathes for them?
InProgressResponse: I find a nice flower wreathe to heighten any bright and cheerful moment. And their return shall be so!
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: You have a fine eye for color. Yes, these will do nicely. I will save the extras for another time, perhaps dry them. That seems appropriate.

Title: Waste Not, Want Not
Description: Retrieve the fallen belongings of cultists who have failed their final rite.
PlayerPrompt: "Is that it? They just… don't come back?"
ObjectiveProposalResponse: Not as themselves, no. They likely still linger in the forest in a more… lacking state. A soulless state, one could say.\n\nIf you want to see for yourself, there is more you can do.
InProgressResponse: Everything we do is to strengthen the cult. No one individual rises above that goal. Not even myself. Not even the High Sage.
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: You went into the forest? Oh, this curiosity of mine is consuming! Tell me, tell me, what did you see? What happened to them?

Title: Where You Go, I Will Follow
Description: Help Han Fang reunite with Han Liu.
PlayerPrompt: "I do not think she will leave them."
ObjectiveProposalResponse: I think you are right. I have a terrible choice to make. I can continue to beg her to leave. She will push me away, perhaps forever. Or… I can let her be, and risk her enduring the same fate as the others.
InProgressResponse: I hope she will hear me out, this time.
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: Why is my mother here? What did she say? I hope she does not mean to lecture me AGAIN.

Title: Medicinal Qualities
Description: Collect medicinal herbs from Lough Du Lac swamp to help Sai Khanam recover from her wounds.
ObjectiveProposalResponse: Not unscathed, I'm afraid. They came while we were resting and upended everything. It seemed as though they were searching for something.\n\nAnd these wounds are… worrying.
InProgressResponse: I am in no immediate danger, but I am in considerable pain. Any help you can offer is appreciated.
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: You found them! What fine specimens. The soil here must be very fertile. \n\nI will make a poultice. It will prevent infection and deal with some of this pain. I am in your debt.

Title: Thieves in the Night
Description: Find and retrieve Sai Khanam's stolen belongings.
ObjectiveProposalResponse: It seems that way, doesn't it? I cannot fathom what I could have in my possession that would interest a dryad.\n\nRegardless, I cannot continue my journey without my things. Can you recover them for me?
InProgressResponse: It was very dark when they came, but I believe they ran to the west of here, up the slope behind me. Thank you again for your aid.
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: Ah! You found them! And mostly intact, too. Did the wolf come with you?

Title: Here, Boy!
Description: Help Sai Khanam track down her wolf companion.
ObjectiveProposalResponse: After you left, he turned to me and simply plucked my bow out of my hands with his teeth! It caught me off guard, and by the time I thought to chase him, he was gone.\n\nCould you find him for me?
InProgressResponse: We have not traveled together long, but already I cannot imagine going on without him. I hope this is not the end of our companionship.
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: Hello, human. I am afraid I cannot return my companion's bow to you.

Title: Scout's Big Secret
Description: Return to Sai Khanam and give her the totem Scout gave you.
PlayerPrompt: "I did not come for the bow."
ObjectiveProposalResponse: You are not? Ah… Sai must be worried about me.\n\nWhat a strange thing, to be bound to one of your kind. Our aims are so often opposed.
InProgressResponse: Please do not share the fact that I can speak with her. I will tell her, in my own time and my own way.
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: He came back! And-- what is this carving? Did you make this?\n\nI will cherish this, as I cherish him. I suppose I should finally choose a name for him, eh?

Title: The Work You Undid
Description: Replant the medicinal herbs you stole to their proper place within Lough Du Lac.
ObjectiveProposalResponse: I suppose it would look like a swamp to one such as yourself. Damp, smells of mold, and rampant with life. Offensive to human noses, no doubt.\n\nNo matter. I would have you restore the herbs that you stole.
InProgressResponse: We have little to say to one another until you have completed the task at hand.
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: I will say this about your kind; You are remarkably efficient.\n\nI know your customs. You expect a reward of coin in exchange for the work of your hands. Consider it done.

Title: Waiting on the Wind
Description: Now that the wind is right, climb to the top of the bridge Avernal Verdure and burst the plant bulbs to release their pollen.
ObjectiveProposalResponse: I keep an aerial garden above the canopy, just east of here. You can find it atop a crumbling bridge.\n\nThe wind is right to burst the bulbs I have cultivated. The smallest pressure will do.
InProgressResponse: You can use your feet to burst them, if it pleases you.
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: I can see from the pollen on your boots that the deed is done. Soon all of Edengrove will become my garden.\n\nHere is your payment, human.

Title: Even Greater Heights
Description: Help Hedera expand her garden by climbing the ruins and planting a flower seed at its highest point.
ObjectiveProposalResponse: To the point. Efficient, as I said.\n\nThere are ruins atop the rise to the north. It is one of the highest points in Edengrove. Ascend the stone and nestle this seedling amongst the cracks at its pinnacle.
InProgressResponse: Try not to fall. Your bones are fragile, I have heard.
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: In time, the bloom will mature and the wind will carry its scent far and wide. It is a species I have cultivated from my own body. A point of pride for my kind.\n\nI am finished with your services. Take your reward.

Title: Hold Your Breath
Description: Destroy the strange flowers clinging to the rocks, ideally without breathing in their scent.
ObjectiveProposalResponse: Let me… gather my thoughts. Just hold on. I had it. It was right there.\n\nYes! Flowers. Big ones. Red. Do NOT breathe their scent.
InProgressResponse: Do. Not. Smell. The. Flowers.
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: How strange. They are gone, but the scent remains.\n\nDo you smell it? Are you afflicted too?!

Title: A Dark Compulsion
Description: Clear the path to the north and west to allow Ranger Yasin to pass unharmed to… wherever it is he is going.
ObjectiveProposalResponse: I know how it sounds. I hear myself. My feet will move me down this path either way. I can FEEL her, waiting.\n\nHow do I know this? Sahal! Wake yourself!
InProgressResponse: It is taking every ounce of will I have to stay here. Please, clear the way.
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse:
Where is she? I am here! I saw it in my mind!

Ranger, shake yourself out of it.

Just… hold a moment. Let me think. Let me breathe.

Title: Crying Out for Love
Description: Ascend the rise and light a bonfire to help signal Ranger Yasin's presence to his "love."
ObjectiveProposalResponse: I am speaking to you with all the sincerity in my heart.\n\nIf I do not find her, I will die. I know it, like I know my own name. My heart will shatter in my chest.
InProgressResponse: She will see it, and she will come. She will see it, and she will come!\n\nShe must…
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: Move aside! Surely she must--\n\n

Title: Out of His Misery
Description: Speak to the dryad Hedera to find a way to rid Ranger Yasin of his affliction.
ObjectiveProposalResponse: My feet are bound to this spot as a tree is rooted to the earth. I can do nothing to change my fate… but you can.\n\nFind her. Find my love, and beg her to end this torment. Please.
InProgressResponse: I feel wretched. Like my heart is being rent from my chest. Please, hurry.
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: Ah. You lived. Thank you for dealing with that nuisance.\n\nI believe I owe you coin, as per your custom.

Title: The Pioneer's Lament
Description: Help a doomed farmer move on with his life.
ObjectiveProposalResponse: Forgive me, I’ve made a horrible, horrible mistake. I tried to start a farm in Edengrove. I moved my family here. We were to harvest paradise. Fool! \n\nThe Angry Earth didn’t take kindly to their new neighbors.
InProgressResponse: Go to my farm, fight off the Angry Earth who have claimed it, and retrieve my farming equipment. And perhaps some token of my family. I am a broken, lonely man.
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: You found my equipment, thank god. But what’s this? A letter from my son? He says he’s raising a farm in Ebonscale Reach, the brave, resourceful lad.

Title: Art is Suffering
Description: Deface an avant-garde sculptress's embarrassing early work.
ObjectiveProposalResponse: Ahem. Like all great artists, I was in a state of deep meditation. Creativity means surrender, not control. It took me centuries to learn that.
InProgressResponse: Dispose of some poorly aged sculptures from my formative years. They no longer accurately reflect my artistic voice, not to mention I used several ex-lovers as models. It’s all best forgotten.
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: All gone? Thank the Muses! Someday I shall memorialize your deeds in marble. \n\nI’m in my “Contra-Formic, Manneristic-Deconstructivism” period, so expect to see an arbitrary number of limbs and a loose sense of shape.

Title: Heart Beats Hate
Description: Harvest the heart of Aeternum's angriest Dryad Brute, for science.
ObjectiveProposalResponse: Ay, look at yon Dryad Brute. Just stares at that tower all day, seething. Fascinating. \n\n‘Balor the Belligerent,’ I call him. I’ve never seen a creature so consumed with hatred.  How I’d love to peek into his heart.
InProgressResponse: There’s a Dryad Brute called Balor the Belligerent. I need his heart. His beautiful, hate-filled heart. Kill him and bring it to me, if you would be so kind.
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: You have the heart, do you? Very resourceful. Look at that, pumping rage and venom. Once I distill it I’ll be capable of the same.

Title: Wyldwood Water
Description: Find the Wyldwood Water recipe for Antara.
ObjectiveProposalResponse: Hah. I only want to continue my mother's legacy. I want to find the potion she said would help us see the world as it really is. \n\nBased on our research, the Dryads should have it here. Will you help me find it?
InProgressResponse: Did you find the recipe? \n\nIt should be in one of the chests on this bridge.
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: Wonderful! I can’t believe it. You found the recipe for Wyldwood Water! \n\nI wish my mother was here to see this.

Title: Everywhere Friends
Description: Understand the message Antara's mother wanted to convey through the Wyldwood Water.
PlayerPrompt: "As an immortal, I like taking risks."
ObjectiveProposalResponse: Hah, clever! Yes, we can't really die on this island. And you seem to have enough spirit to keep from turning Lost. \n\nReady, then? Let's have the Wyldwood Water and see what happens.
InProgressResponse: How are you feeling?  \n\nDo you notice anything different about the nature around you?
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: I'm glad you're here with me. \n\nI guess the universe works in strange ways and I'm lucky you came to the bridge when you did.

Title: Incomparable Blue
Description: Return the misplaced easel to Pietr Wolcott.
ObjectiveProposalResponse: (The painting has been signed by a P. Wolcott. \n\nUpon closer inspection, there's a note asking for it to be returned if found.)
InProgressResponse: (The painting has been signed by a P. Wolcott. \n\nUpon closer inspection, there's a note asking for it to be returned if found.)
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: What a gorgeous blue! It's so close to the shade I imagined. \n\nMaybe you do have the makings of an artist, if you ever choose to drop the sword and pick up a brush instead, which seems unlikely.

Title: Clamorous Vox
Description: Collect the pieces to Clamorous Vox for Ranger Madaki to assemble.
ObjectiveProposalResponse: There's no better feeling than a musket in your hands, the power of fire, steel, and science.\n\nThere might even be an opportunity to craft a wholly unique firearm, if you're interested.
InProgressResponse: Madaki has the designs. You need only supply the parts.
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: You've acquired the parts for the Clamorous Vox. \n\nVery well, then you shall have it. A finer musket the world has never known. Wield it well.

Title: Azoth is the Glue
Description: Gather Azoth-Infused Resin from Angry Earth in Tor Fearg.

Title: Glinting Gold
Description: Gather Golden Flintlock from Lost in Periville.

Title: Barrel Down
Description: Gather Precision-Engineered Barrel from Corrupted in Greater Tribulation.

Title: The Ramrod
Description: Gather Ramrod from Corrupted in Svikin's Stand.

Title: Trigger-Happy
Description: Gather Hair Trigger from Undead in Stone Skull Fort.

Title: Seakissed Wood
Description: Gather Seakissed Wood from Angry Earth in Eridanus.

Title: Heavy is the Base
Description: Gather Shock-Absorbent Base from Corrupted in Scorpius.

Title: Take Stock of the Heart
Description: Gather Impossibly Sturdy Vines from Angry Earth in Malevolence.

Title: Blessing the Rains
Description: Gather the materials necessary to create Torrent, the legendary bow.
ObjectiveProposalResponse: Yes, well, if you have sharp eyes, and indeed, you must, if you spotted me here. \n\nThis bow is the mighty Torrent, a bow of legend among the rangers. Acquire these items and it shall be yours.
InProgressResponse: The Torrent would be the envy of any archer in Aeternum.\n\nA weapon without equal, I think.
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: You've got it all, eh? Otherworldly sinew, ancient bone, an oil coat, and a perfect string for a perfected draw. \n\nTake this bow, the Torrent, and wield it with pride. It's in a class all of its own.

Title: Undead Sagittary
Description: Travel to Periville and collect pieces of Pallid Ash Wood from the Undead.

Title: Bewitched Thumbring
Description: Travel to the Spilaio Cavern and collect fragments of Bewitched Bone from Ancient Guardians.

Title: Sea-crossing Arrow
Description: Travel to the Stone Skull Fort and collect pieces of Seakissed Oak Wood from Pirates.

Title: Vantage Point
Description: Climb the tallest tower in Edengrove, Malevolence, and collect Perfected Hemp String from Alcazarian Archers.

Title: Palm of Hand
Description: Brave Scorpius in Mourningdale and collect a piece of Codex-binding Leather from S'ylanx.

Title: Fine Oil Coat
Description: Travel to the Scorched Mines and collect Scorchvein Oil from Corrupted mineworkers.

Title: Toxic Toxophilite
Description: Travel to the Mangled Heights and collect pieces of Blackened Sinew from Unhallowed Tendrils.

Title: The Remaining Spirit
Description: Travel to Eridanus and collect pieces of Enchanted Azoth Wood from Eridanite Yeoman.

Title: The Reformation
Description: Recover the components needed to create the Greataxe called Reformation, then deliver them to Ranger Madaki in Mountainhome.
ObjectiveProposalResponse: I do. The Corrupted call this design 'the Reformation', and though I despise them, I like the name.\n\nGather the components on this list and bring them to Madaki. Then the Reformation will be yours to wield.
InProgressResponse: Have you ever noticed how the Corrupted smell? \n\nIt's like some kind of sulfuric body odor mixed with spoiled fruit. Dreadful.
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: Here we are, you've acquired the components for the Greataxe. \n\nWell done, this is an axe destined to fell many Corrupted. Wield it with savage fury, {playerName}. Give them something to fear.

Title: A King's Defense
Description: Gather components to create the legendary tower shield Rook's Defense.
ObjectiveProposalResponse: I do. Using a shield, and one like this in particular, requires a strategy all of its own.\n\nIt's like a game I once played called 'Chess'; this shield is like the Rook to defend your King.
InProgressResponse: There is no shield I have ever seen as formidable as the Rook's Defense will be.\n\nAssuming you follow through and get Madaki to forge it, that is.
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: A masterful game you've played, acquiring these components.\n\n You've earned Rook's Defense, and will doubtlessly wield it with the same impressive valor. Checkmate, indeed.

Title: Chaturanga Opening
Description: The classical opening and setting of the board from the Indian game Chatur that would later inspire Chess. Your opening lies in Malevolence.

Title: White's First Move
Description: In this deadly game of Chess, the ivory pieces move first. Your first move is to Scorpius.

Title: En Passant
Description: The ability of the Pawn to dash forward to the front lines in its first play is a formidable move. Your next move takes you to Eridanus.

Title: Shahnameh's Story
Description: The Persian story of Shahnameh, the reenacting of an epic battle on a Chess board. Your battle continues in Periville.

Title: The Touch-Move Rule
Description: Once a piece has been touched on the Chess board it must be moved. Your next move takes you to Stone Skull Fort.

Title: The Pawn's Promotion
Description: Should a Pawn make it to the other side of the board alive it will be crowned a Queen. Your crowning comes in Caminus.

Title: Castling the King
Description: Castling is a move in Chess wherein the King moves two squares towards a Rook, and then the Rook moves to protect their King’s flank. Castle yourself in Mangled Heights.

Title: Rook's Checkmate
Description: An announcement that the other player's King has been placed in a position of peril. Check the Corrupted of Opulence.
